<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Mass2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Mass,</orth> the service of the Romish church: <cit><quote>at evening m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 1, 38</bibl></cit> (== vespers). <emph>M.</emph> and <emph>by the m.</emph> used as forms of asseveration; <cit><quote>m.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.106" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 106</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.101" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.7.9" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.4.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 4, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 62</bibl>. <cit><quote>by the m.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.214" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 214</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 4.2.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 2, 53</bibl> (Q <emph>by m.</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.400" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 400</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.115" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 115</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.3.16" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 3, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.395" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 395</bibl>. Sometimes omitted in Ff, probably as indecent: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 1, 18</bibl>. B <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 1, 50</bibl>. Sometimes changed: <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.73" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 73</bibl> (Ff <emph>look</emph>). <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.384" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 384</bibl> (Ff <emph>in troth</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>